Subject: [ghostium] AudioBuffer readback noise hook

Spec-D wiring. Anchors at top of ``audio_buffer.cc``. The real call
into ``FingerprintNoiseSource::ApplyAudioNoise`` lands inside both
``getChannelData`` (returns a Float32Array view of the per-channel PCM
buffer) and ``copyFromChannel`` (copies a chunk into a caller-supplied
buffer). Per plan.md section 4.6, the perturbation is ±1e-7 - well
below the noise floor of any consumer audio path.

The ``sample_index_base`` parameter is the absolute sample index of
the first element so that chunked reads via ``copyFromChannel`` get a
consistent noise pattern regardless of chunking.

